If you want a simpler and less invasive "improved cd", you can do this in ZSH:    chpwd() {
        ls
    }

It does what it says: after changing the cwd, list its contents. You can try other things, e.g. "[ -d .git ] && git status".

I tried zoxide, but at the end settled for using fzf to quickly find and enter directories:  qcd () {
   local d
   dirs=$(fd -t d -t l --ignore-file ~/.gitignore . $@)
   d="$(echo ${dirs} | fzf +m --height=50%)"  && cd "${d}"
  }

  alias hd="qcd ${HOME}"
